observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to:
a. Regularly check and update the Inventory Committee membership to make sure that all members are active in service and adjust the composition as needed to maintain an effective oversight team;
b. Instruct the Inventory Committee to
(i) conduct actual physical count of all PPE of the Municipality on or before January 31 of each year;
(ii)reconcile the inventory reports with the accounting records; and
(iii) promptly submit the related RPCPPE to the Audit Team;
c. Ensure that the Property Officer maintain property cards, to effectively oversee and manage the agency's properties; and
d. Task the Inventory Committee in prioritizing the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances as per COA Circular No. 2020-006 to address historical reliability issues in financial statements. Allocate dedicated time and resources, including relieving the inventory committee of regular duties, to conduct thorough inventory verification and reconciliation activities on PPE accounts.

