Recommendation:
We recommended to the management to do the following:
Issue written notices to the concerned employees to immediately file their leave applications, otherwise, their salaries and wages may be withheld corresponding to the period of absences;
Issue a written demand to the Sangguniang Bayan (SB) to submit a copy of the lacking Minutes of Regular Sessions;
Instruct the Human Resources in-charge to expedite the recording and reconciliation of absences in the individual leave cards of the employees and submit the lacking leave applications and Minutes of Regular Sessions to the Office of the COA Auditor for review;
Issue an office order to remind the officials and employees to follow the prescribed periods of filing the applications for leave of absence;
For the succeeding period, instruct the Human Resources Management Officer to follow the procedure below in monitoring the accumulated leave credits:
Use Microsoft Excel in monitoring the accumulated leave credits of each LGU official and employee. Based on the balances shown in the individual leave cards after reconciliation, input the balances as of December 31, 2024 in Microsoft Excel. This becomes the beginning balance for CY 2025. Provide a column for leave credits earned, and another column for consumed leave credits;
Before approving any application for leave, always check the leave credit balance and make sure that the balance can cover the number of days to be availed by the official/employee;
At the end of each month, record the leave credits earned by each official/ employee in the individual leave card and/or electronic monitoring of accumulated leave credits;
At the end of each month (for regular employees) or each quincena (for casual employees), notify the officials and employees of the submission of their Daily Time Records (DTRs), minutes of regular session, leave applications, travel orders, and certificates of appearance. Collate the documents, check the actual absences of the officials/employees and reconcile the actual absences with the approved leave applications, and check the dates of officials travels and reconcile the dates with the travel orders and certificates of appearance;
For travels without certificates of appearance, require the official/employee to submit any other proof of completed travel, otherwise, consider it as unauthorized leave of absence;
Record the absences in the individual leave card and/or electronic monitoring of accumulated leave credits, as follows:
For absences supported with leave applications, deduct the number of days availed from the accumulated leave credits of the official/employee;
For absences without leave applications, notify the concerned official/employee in writing to file his application for leave and/or submit to the HR Office his approved leave application within three (3) calendar days from receipt of notice, otherwise, consider his absence as unauthorized. Once his approved leave application is received, record his absence in the individual leave card and/or electronic monitoring of accumulated leave credits;
Once absences are recorded, submit the DTRs, minutes of session, leave applications, travel orders, and certificates of appearance to the Accounting Office for attachment to the payrolls; and
Instruct the Municipal Accounting Office to:
Check the completeness of supporting documents for the payment of salaries and wages before submitting the same to the Office of the COA Auditor; and
Withhold in the next payroll the salaries of those with unauthorized absences.

