We recommended to the management to do the following:

Require the Purchasing Unit to forward all the POs to the GSO in order to properly monitor the delivery of the goods purchased;

Require the Municipal Accountant to –

Make the necessary adjusting entries effecting the changes in accounting policy as directed under the above COA circular and submit to this office the journal entry vouchers supported with supporting documents for verification by the team;

Subsequently, upon purchase, debit an inventory account to record the delivery of semi-expendable property then upon issuance to end-user by the GSO, require the submission of documents, then credit the respective inventory account then recognize an expense. 

