Require the assigned canvassers to make sure that the date signed/received by the supplier are indicated on the POs/Contracts and NTPs, and avoid alterations/erasures, otherwise, have the alterations/erasures countersigned by the supplier or his authorized representative;

Require the GSO to properly monitor the delivery of goods purchased, fill-up the actual date of receipt on the delivery receipts, and avoid alterations/erasures, otherwise, personally countersign the alterations/erasures or authorize someone to countersign the same; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to properly compute and impose liquidated damages for late deliveries.

We recommended to the management to –

Require the Municipal Accountant to properly compute and impose liquidated damages for late deliveries;

Collect from the concerned suppliers the liquidated damages, otherwise, require the officials concerned to pay for the liquidated damages. If remained unpaid, the team will issue the corresponding Notice of Disallowance.

We recommended to the Management to instruct the Municipal Accountant to:

Submit the lacking supporting documents identified in Annex L;

Review and deduct the liquidated damages due from the contractor from the latter’s unpaid claims from the LGU;

Avoid unauthorized alterations on the supporting documents;

Check the coherence and correctness of the amounts and other information on the supporting documents; and

Record capitalizable expenses in the proper asset account.

We recommended the following –

The management to strictly implement the minimum requirements set forth under COA Circular 77-61, to wit:
Revise the existing Vehicle Trip Ticket and Request for Fuel and Oil to conform with the forms prescribed under the circular and ensure that the forms are serially numbered and all the information are properly and completely filled-up;
Preparation and submission of reports prescribed under the circular;
Ensure that original copy of the invoice and the pre-numbered gas withdrawal slip/ request for fuel and oil is obtained immediately after withdrawal of fuel and is properly filled-up;
Issue Memorandum as to who may approve the withdrawal of fuel whenever the Mayor or the Executive Assistant is unable to sign the document.

The concerned Head of Office to issue written authorization as to who may sign in their behalf as the requisitioner whenever they are not present and ensure that the name thereof are written in the forms;

Ensure that the disbursements for fuel, oil, and lubricants are supported with complete documents such as Statement of Account (SOA), gas withdrawal slip, charge invoice, and the trip ticket (data in all documents must coincide with each other).

